 down and be replaced by mehrotra effective may   mehrotras background includes cofounding sandisk in  and serving as its president and ceo from  until its acquisition in  by western digital prior to serving as ceo of sandisk mehrotra had been the chief operating officer head of engineering and chief of product development under mehrotras leadership sandisks annual revenue peaked at  billion and the company sold for  billion in  to western digital with long experience leading a major memory manufacturer mehrotra is one of the most highlyqualified candidates possible to take over at micron outgoing ceo mark durcan will be stepping down as ceo and from the board of directors effective may  but plans to stay on as an advisor until early august mehrotra plans to divide his time between micron headquarters in boise idaho and microns silicon valley offices in milpitas california a few blocks from sandisk headquarters source micron tweet print this article post your comment please log in or sign up to comment post a comment  comments view all comments helvete  thursday july    link neat reply pipeline stories  submit news benq announces zowie xl ‘esports’ display  fhd  hz dyac ulmb tech dell’s ultrasharp udw now available curved ” × usbc  maingear launches r razer edition miniitx system with amd ryzen or intel core i adata launches isss and imp industrial ssds d nand extreme temps alphacool releases two new ssd coolers passive hdx and watercooled hdx asus introduces rog crosshair vi extreme am motherboard for ryzen intel launches movidius neural compute stick deep learning and ai on a  usb stick ekwb releases new rgb monoblock for msi x motherboards kontron merges with st gets access to software manufacturing samsung increases production volumes of  gb hbm chips due to growing demand intel releases graphics driver  for windows gigabyte announces hda motherboard for mining rigs the mining cart rolls on tweets ryansmithat mcverhoef anandtech sorry we dont have one planned at